---
layout: layouts/base.njk
order: 6
title: Live demo
description: A support-message triage model running entirely in your browser on WebGPU — no server, fully private. A live demonstration of quantized, on-device small-model inference.
ogType: website
---
<section class="container-x py-16 md:py-24">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
    <p class="eyebrow">Live demo · on-device inference</p>
    <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl font-bold leading-[1.08] tracking-tightest text-ink-900 md:text-5xl dark:text-white">
      A language model that never leaves your browser.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 text-lg prose-muted">
      Paste a support message and a <strong>1.58-bit</strong>, 1.7-billion-parameter model
      triages it — <strong>category, urgency, and a one-line summary</strong> — running
      entirely on your device via <strong>WebGPU</strong>. Nothing is sent to a server.
      It's a live demonstration of the same quantized, sovereign, on-device inference we
      build for clients.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 text-sm prose-muted">
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-teal-500/30 bg-teal-50 px-3 py-1 font-medium text-teal-700 dark:bg-teal-500/10 dark:text-teal-300">100% in your browser · no server</span>
      <span>Needs a WebGPU browser (Chrome/Edge, desktop) with a GPU. First run downloads ~237&nbsp;MB, then runs offline.</span>
    </div>

    <div id="demoWrap" class="mt-8 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 shadow-sm dark:border-white/10">
      <button id="demoLaunch" type="button" data-src="/demo/app/"
              class="flex w-full flex-col items-center justify-center gap-2 bg-white px-6 py-16 text-center dark:bg-ink-950"
              style="min-height:320px">
        <span class="btn-primary pointer-events-none">▶ Launch the live demo</span>
        <span class="mt-2 text-sm prose-muted">Loads ~237&nbsp;MB and runs on your GPU · needs a WebGPU browser</span>
      </button>
    </div>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm prose-muted">
      <a class="underline" href="/demo/app/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Or open it full screen in a new tab ↗</a>
    </p>
    <script>
      document.getElementById("demoLaunch")?.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
        const btn = e.currentTarget, wrap = document.getElementById("demoWrap");
        const f = document.createElement("iframe");
        f.src = btn.dataset.src; f.title = "On-device message triage demo";
        f.setAttribute("allow", "webgpu; fullscreen"); f.setAttribute("loading", "eager");
        f.style.cssText = "display:block;width:100%;height:78vh;min-height:560px;border:0";
        wrap.innerHTML = ""; wrap.appendChild(f);
      });
    </script>

    <div class="mt-8 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200/70 bg-white/60 p-5 text-sm prose-muted dark:border-white/10 dark:bg-ink-950/40">
      <p class="font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-white">Model credits &amp; license</p>
      <p class="mt-2">
        Demonstrator model: <strong>Bonsai-1.7B</strong> (Q1_0, 1-bit) — ©&nbsp;Prism&nbsp;ML,
        Apache-2.0 (<a class="underline" href="https://huggingface.co/prism-ml/Bonsai-1.7B-gguf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">model card</a>,
        <a class="underline" href="https://prismml.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">prismml.com</a>).
        WebGPU engine adapted from the
        <a class="underline" href="https://huggingface.co/spaces/webml-community/bonsai-webgpu-kernels" target="_blank" rel="noopener">webml-community / Xenova</a> demo (MIT).
      </p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-xs">
        Bonsai is an independent open model from Prism&nbsp;ML, shown here purely to demonstrate
        on-device quantized inference. It is not one of sysf.io's Apertus fine-tunes.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
